izabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth had at least 1 son and 3 daughters with John Boyville."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1391–1467":"1391–1467","1415–1467":"1415–1467","1422–1480":"1422–1480","1433–1468":"1433–1468","1440–1515":"1440–1515","–Female":"Surnud","1415":"1415","1468":"1468","1467":"1467","about 1415":"umbes 1415","1422":"1422","1433":"1433","1440":"1440","about 1440":"umbes 1440","1480":"1480","1391":"1391","1515":"1515","Stockerstone, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Stoke by Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Stoke by Ipswich, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1391–1467":"1391–1467","1415–1467":"1415–1467","1422–1480":"1422–1480","1433–1468":"1433–1468","1440–1515":"1440–1515","–Female":"Kuollut","1415":"1415","1468":"1468","1467":"1467","about 1415":"noin 1415","1422":"1422","1433":"1433","1440":"1440","about 1440":"noin 1440","1480":"1480","1391":"1391","1515":"1515","Stockerstone, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Stoke by Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Stoke by Ipswich, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1391–1467":"1391–1467","1415–1467":"1415–1467","1422–1480":"1422–1480","1433–1468":"1433–1468","1440–1515":"1440–1515","–Female":"Décédée","1415":"1415","1468":"1468","1467":"1467","about 1415":"environ 1415","1422":"1422","1433":"1433","1440":"1440","about 1440":"environ 1440","1480":"1480","1391":"1391","1515":"1515","Stockerstone, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","Suffolk, Eng